(Pharmacology Review: Warfarin \(Coumadin\)) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Warfarin is an oral anticoagulant medication used to prevent blood clots, deep vein thrombosis \(DVT\), and pulmonary embolism \(PE\). It works by inhibiting vitamin K-dependent clotting factors.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Key Nursing Interventions:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(1. Monitor International Normalized Ratio \(INR\) regularly. The therapeutic range for most patients is 2.0 to 3.0.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(2. Monitor for signs of bleeding, including hematuria, epistaxis, melena, and petechiae.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(3. Educate the patient to maintain a consistent intake of foods high in Vitamin K \(e.g., green leafy vegetables\), as sudden changes can affect warfarin efficacy.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(4. The antidote for warfarin toxicity or overdose is Vitamin K \(phytonadione\).) Tj
0 -15 Td
ET
